A four-year-old girl, Esther Olisa, has been abducted by gunmen suspected to be kidnappers in Ondo State. The gunmen, who were said to be four in number, abducted the girl at Danjuma neighborhood of Akure, the state capital. According to sources, the victim was kidnapped from her father’s home. The gunmen had allegedly robbed the victim’s family of their belongings before abducting Esther and fleeing in a black Toyota Camry Sedan. Mr. Oga Olisa, the girl’s father, confirmed that the case had been reported to Akure’s “B” Divisional Police Station. Confirming the incident, the Police Public Relations Officer in the State, SP Fumilayo Odunlami, said investigation had commenced towards rescuing the girl.